    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/3773</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: Although you have received a
                    copy of this message<note n="9" xml:id="d5fn1">Memorandum from the Guatemalan
                        Minister of Foreign Affairs to the American Minister in Guatemala, <ref
                            target="frus1917Supp01v01#pg_258">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, supp. 1, p.
                        258</ref>.</note> I desire to call your attention particularly to it and to
                    receive from you directions as to what reply we should make.</p>
                <p>I believe that it would be for our interest to have Guatemala in the war, and
                    very possibly Honduras, as it would offer a constant check upon Mexico in case
                    its Government should adopt any measures in the interest of Germany.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
